Q1\ Install Openssh in ubuntu using apt
A1\ $sudo apt install openssh

Q2\ update the apt List
A2\ $sudo apt-get update

Q3\ install VLC player
A3\ $sudo apt-get install vlcplayer 

Q4\ change your DNS to 8.8.8.8 and 8.8.4.4
A4\ $sudo apt install openresolv 
    $sudo apt install resolvconf
    $sudo mousepad /etc/network/interfaces
     type inside the mousepad text editing: 
     dns-nameserver 8.8.8.8
     dns-nameserver 8.8.4.4
     save the changes
    $resolvconf -u
    $mousepad /etc/network/interfaces
    

Q5\ Secure the SSH ( put all what you know in the configuration file)


Q6\ How can you find out how much memory Linux is using?
A6\ $df -ih
    or
    #gparted

